Peter Jennings, the iconic ABC News anchor, has been diagnosed with lung cancer at 66.
Despite his illness, he plans to continue anchoring "World News Tonight" during treatment.
Colleagues and industry experts express support and admiration for Jennings' dedication and impact on broadcast journalism.
His decision to forgo surgery indicates a challenging prognosis, but his resilience and commitment to his work shine through.
Viewers and colleagues alike are moved by his openness about his health struggles, drawing parallels to other public figures who have shared their battles with illness.
Jennings' presence and influence in the news industry remain unparalleled.
